A pair of suicide bombers struck outside Nato's largest base in southern Afghanistan today killing 23 civilians and wounding 50 in one of the bloodiest attacks in recent weeks.              

A
bomber on a motorcycle first blew himself up in a parking lot outside Kandahar  
airbase which was packed with truck drivers and other civilians waiting to get into the 
facility. 

A few minutes later, as people 
gathered at the site of the blast, another bomber on foot walked into 
the crowd and detonated his explosives, said Ahmad Faisal, a spokesman 
for the provincial governor.    

