Violence has surged across Afghanistan since the Taliban began a spring offensive in April, vowing to target the Afghan government and security forces, as well as the 130,000 foreign troops in the country.          

Kandahar, the birthplace of the Taliban, has seen some of the worst attacks.   

The violence has stoked concern that 
Afghan forces may struggle against a Taliban insurgency at its deadliest
once most Western combat troops leave by the end of 
2014.                

Ahead
of the handover, foreign and Afghan forces have stepped up operations 
in the southern and eastern strongholds of the Taliban.    

On Wednesday, the coalition and Afghan
forces conducted an operation in the Baraki Barak district of Logar 
province against a Taliban commander.         

